  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 10 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 5 critical, 13 high, 7 medium, 14 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and Iaşi (IAS/LRIA); plus 15 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Iaşi (IAS/LRIA) and Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP). Network hotspots: Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM) and 5 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, very low visibility and RVR limitations. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Turku (TKU/EFTU) and 9 others.",
  "detail90": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 10 airports right now. Base airports (focus): Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR) — HIGH: mist; strong gusts risk | Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) — HIGH: freezing fog; cold-temperature performance penalties; visibility down to 500 m | Iaşi (IAS/LRIA) — CRIT: freezing fog; cold-temperature performance penalties; visibility down to 600 m, cloud base around 100 ft | Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI) — HIGH: fog; visibility down to 800 m, cloud base around 100 ft; forecast below approach minima at times | Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) — CRIT: freezing fog; cold-temperature performance penalties; visibility down to 200 m, RVR down to 500 m, cloud base around 100 ft | Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) — HIGH: fog; strong gusts risk; visibility down to 700 m and 12 others. Worst affected now: Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ) — CRIT: fog; visibility down to 150 m, RVR down to 600 m, cloud base around 200 ft; below approach minima (current METAR) (drivers: low-visibility procedures (reduced capacity), runway visual range (RVR) constraints, approach minima limits) | Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ) — CRIT: fog; visibility down to 100 m, RVR down to 650 m, cloud base around 200 ft; below alternate minima (current METAR) (drivers: low-visibility procedures (reduced capacity), runway visual range (RVR) constraints, approach minima limits) | Keflavik (KEF/BIKF) — CRIT: snow; cold-temperature performance penalties; visibility down to 2 km, cloud base around 400 ft (drivers: cold-temperature performance penalties, low ceilings, snow/blowing snow) | Turku (TKU/EFTU) — CRIT: fog; snow; runway contamination risk (drivers: low-visibility takeoff restrictions, runway visual range (RVR) constraints, approach minima limits) | Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM) — CRIT: snow; cold-temperature performance penalties; visibility down to 800 m, cloud base around 400 ft (drivers: cold-temperature performance penalties, very low visibility, low ceilings) | Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG) — CRIT: fog; snow; visibility down to 200 m, cloud base around 100 ft (drivers: low-visibility procedures (reduced capacity), runway visual range (RVR) constraints, approach minima limits) and 4 others. Changed since last run: Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Stockholm Skavsta (NYO/ESKN), Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Federico Fellini (RMI/LIPR), Marche (AOI/LIPY), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN) and 2 others.",
